# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

Inorder Traversal of BST is always sorted.
Inorder = left, root, right
root = mid of sorted array

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
**Divide and Conquer and Inorder Traversal**
$$Inorder = left, root, right$$ which means root = mid of sorted Array
Divide the array into smaller pieces using recursion and assing root = mid 
$$ mid = (start+end)/2;$$



# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n) 
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
